OL,3,CTrump's Irish merger comment 'clearly
OL,4,Ca joke', says deputy First Minister
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the President's suggestion
OL,7,Fof an Irish merger was "clearly a
OL,8,Fjoke", Emma Little-Pengelly said.
OL,10,FIt came at the start of the
OL,11,Fpresident's address to the annual
OL,12,FSpeakers' Friends of Ireland Luncheon
OL,13,Fat Capitol Hill on Tuesday.
OL,15,FMr Trump had been welcoming some of
OL,16,Fthe notable guests to the event,
OL,17,Fincluding Taoiseach Micheal Martin and
OL,18,Fdeputy First Minister, Ms Little-
OL,19,FPengelly, when he observed: "They get
OL,20,Falong so well."
OL,26,@oD@XOU{D@]OU|D@OO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
