CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773929472
OL,3,CTrump's Irish merger comment 'clearly
OL,4,Ca joke', says deputy First Minister
OL,6,FLooking towards the two, he added: "I
OL,7,Fsaw that, you get along very well
OL,8,Ftogether, I don't know if I should be
OL,9,Fpromoting merger, I love mergers."
OL,11,FAs most in the room laughed, Mr Trump
OL,12,Fadded: "We're going to get into more
OL,13,Ftrouble with that than the beauty", in
OL,14,Freference to a comment he had made
OL,15,Fearlier describing a woman he had
OL,16,Fcalled out as beautiful.
OL,26,@nD@dOUqD@bO]tD@HOUuD@bO]
